The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                Two persons were injured in separate accidents in the city on Wednesday. Mantu Shaw, 12, suffered leg injuries after a lorry knocked him down at the Tirreti Bazaar crossing early on Wednesday. He was admitted to Calcutta Medical College and Hospital and later shifted to a nursing home. The lorry driver fled.  ohammad Iqbal, 22, knocked down an unidentified pedestrian while riding a bike at the Rashbehari Avenue crossing on Wednesday morning. Both were taken to MR Bangur Hospital.     Khogendranath Roy, 70, went missing after being released from the medicine ward of Howrah District Hospital on Wednesday morning. Roy, a resident of Liluah, was admitted to the hospital with stomach pain on Tuesday night.    A fire broke out beside a conveyer belt in the departure lounge of the domestic terminal of the airport on Wednesday evening. The blaze was put off in 15 minutes. Three Jet Airways and one JetLite flights were delayed by an hour on an average.    Cellphones and recharge vouchers worth over Rs 1 lakh were stolen from a Barasat shop on Tuesday night.    Deb Kumar Ganguly, a pioneer of geo-physics education in India and a former teacher at IIT Kharagpur, died in a city hospital on May 14. He was 86.    Goons allegedly backed by the CPM attacked five members of a family at Minarait near Calcutta Leather Complex on Wednesday afternoon. Police said trouble broke out after the gang protested the gangs habit of drinking beside their house.            
